My daughter attended Tehiyah from 5th-8th grades.
We were not a particularly observant family and fit in fine there.
There is great diversity at Tehiyah in terms of Jewish observance, beliefs, political views.
It was an incredible experience, both for my daughter and our entire family.
I can't recommend the school enough.
Also, because of the tremendous range of Jewish identities and beliefs, the children learn very quickly what true tolerance means.
As for Oakland Hebrew Day, I have no first hand experience with them.
From reputation, they are more orthodox, probably a narrower range of beliefs and practices represented at the school.
Feel free to contact me directly for more information about Tehiyah.
sb Don't want to beat a dead horse about Tehiyah, but I will say that the academics, emotional environment, administration, and teachers--all great.
